<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-SUNS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURIES HELP CUT ROSTER TO 12 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB YOUNG  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - The Suns trimmed their regular-season roster from 14
players to 12 by placing rookies  &UR; Gerald Brown and  &UR; Toby Bailey on
the injured list.
</P>
<P>
   Brown officially is listed with chondromalacia patella in his
left knee, which is a way of saying he has pain under the kneecap.
</P>
<P>
   Bailey has patellar tendinitis in his right knee.
</P>
<P>
   They join second-year center  &UR; Horacio Llamas, who is out because
of a strained Achilles tendon and bruised right foot, on the
injured list.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns hoped Brown could be their backup point guard, and he
played well in two preseason games, averaging 10.5 points and
hitting 13 of 16 field goal attempts in two exhibition games
against the Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   But without benefit of a regular training camp and a full
preseason, Brown struggled when the regular season began.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm disappointed,'' Brown said. ``It was a lack of preseason
games and less (repetitions), that's about it.''
</P>
<P>
   An undrafted rookie from Pepperdine, Brown was a standout at the
Los Angeles Summer Pro League, where the Suns decided to sign him.
He appeared in six regular-season games, averaging 5.4 minutes and
making 6 of 17 shots.
</P>
<P>
   Bailey, who was drafted by the Los Angeles Lakers in the second
round of last summer's draft and traded to the Suns for future
considerations, played in five regular-season games. &QL; 
Home delivery &QL; 
Suns center  &UR; Luc Longley received his 1998 world championship ring
from the Chicago Bulls, and he didn't even have to leave his house
to get it.
</P>
<P>
   Bulls owner  &UR; Jerry Reinsdorf, who owns a home in the Valley,
delivered the ring to Longley. ``I offered to come get it, but he
said he'd bring it over,'' Longley said.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Joe Kleine, Longley's backup with the Suns and a reserve with
the Bulls last season, also received his championship ring from
Reinsdorf.
</P>
<P>
   ``He sent it COD,'' Kleine joked.
</P>
<P>
   Actually, Kleine received his in the mail about two weeks ago. &QL; 
Scrimmage open &QL; 
The team will hold a scrimmage open to the public at 1 p.m. on
Sunday. Doors at America West Arena will open at noon. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
