<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DRAKE'S RETURN ON HOLD 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By TIM TYERS  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TAMPA _ Coyotes right wing  &UR; Dallas Drake hoped to return Friday
night against Tampa Bay from the separated shoulder that has
sidelined him for the past 10 games. But caution prevailed.
</P>
<P>
   Coach  &UR; Jim Schoenfeld doesn't expect Drake back for the next two
games.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's at least a week away, and I don't think he'll be ready
before the Washington game (Wednesday),'' Schoenfeld said. ``It's
an injury where if you don't have your strength back, you are very
susceptible to reinjuring it.
</P>
<P>
   ``It goes beyond pain. You can have pain and still play, but
it's the strength we're more interested in. He's not going until we
feel he's good and strong. The next one won't be this bad, it'll be
worse. We want to make sure we get him where we're sure he's not
going to have a recurring injury.'' &QL; 
Niki's the man &QL; 
Goalie  &UR; Jimmy Waite was sent to Springfield of the AHL to work on
his confidence and his game, not necessarily in that order, which
leaves untested &UR; Robert Esch as the backup to  &UR; Nikolai Khabibulin.
</P>
<P>
   But don't look for Esch to see much playing time on the Coyotes'
seven-game trip.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't have any hard plan for Robert Esch,'' Schoenfeld said.
``Niki will play again in Florida (tonight), and we'll go from
there. Once you get by the back-to-back games, Niki can almost play
all the rest. Just two things concern us: one, how is Niki doing,
and two, how is Jimmy doing in Springfield. I don't really plan to
put Robert Esch in right now.''
</P>
<P>
   How about if the Coyotes' somehow gain a comfortable lead?
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if there's ever a big enough lead,'' Schoenfeld
said, laughing. ``Wins are too hard to come by.'' &QL; 
Ice chips &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Injured  &UR; Brad Isbister is accompanying the team on the trip,
although he's four weeks away from playing after hernia surgery.
He's merely along to have his rehab regimen monitored by
conditioning coach  &UR; Stieg Theander.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Jim Cummins returned after sitting out a five-game suspension
for elbowing. It was his second suspension of the season. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
