<HEADLINE>
TOYLAND 1999: SHUT THAT THING UP! 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review) 
(NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089) 
(bl) 
 By JENNY LYN BADER   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Remember Giga Pets? Not long ago, the little
hand-held computers that children fed, watered and nurtured by
pressing buttons were all the rage.
</P>
<P>
   It is difficult to imagine how a toy company could top that
craze, but get ready for Giga Monsters, designed for ages 5 and up.
Here the object is to make the virtual pets die.
</P>
