   It's almost enough to make one nostalgic for the days when toys
died because they ran out of batteries.
</P>
<P>
   The Giga Monster was but one of many startling items on display
last week at the 96th American International Toy Fair in New York,
where 1,700 exhibitors gathered to peddle their wares to 20,000
buyers. Most of the toys and games haven't hit stores yet. Some are
still prototypes and failed in demonstrations; others succeeded in
demonstrations and will still fail in stores.
</P>
