 &HT;    Spring training baseball essentials
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   NL EAST
</P>
<P>
   ATLANTA BRAVES
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: Disney's Wide World of Sports (9,500); Lake
Buena Vista, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 106-56 (1st).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Bobby Cox (14th season, 1,063-853; overall,
1,418-1,145).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: 2B Bret Boone, RF Brian Jordan, OF Otis Nixon, LHP
Mike Remlinger.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: SS Rafael Belliard, LHP Norm Charlton, 1B Greg
Colbrunn, RHP Dennis Martinez, LHP Denny Neagle, OF Curtis Pride,
OF Michael Tucker, 1B Andres Galarraga.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: Rookie LHP Bruce Chen becomes a spring
priority after the Braves discarded Neagle to pick up Boone. Kevin
Millwood and Chen, who has the No. 5 job to lose, are prominent
players in a camp short on story lines. Ryan Klesko replaces
Galarraga, out with cancer, at first.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $15.50 lower deck, $13.50 upper deck,
$10.50 general admission. Telephone: 407-939-1500.
</P>
<P>
   FLORIDA MARLINS
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: Space Coast Stadium (7,200), Viera, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Friday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 54-108 (5th).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: John Boles (second season, 40-35).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: LHP Armando Almanza, C Jorge Fabregas, C Guillermo
Garcia, INF Benji Gil, RHP Braden Looper, 3B Mike Lowell, OF Russ
Morman, OF DaRond Stovall and OF Pat Watkins.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: Manager Jim Leyland, 3B Josh Booty, RHP Manny
Barrios, OF John Cangelosi, C Randy Knoor, RHP Eric Ludwick, RHP
Donn Pall, SS Edgar Renteria, UTIL. John Wehner and C Greg Zaun.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: Boles inherits the train wreck of 1998. RHP
Alex Fernandez (rotator cuff) hasn't pitched in 18 months, and the
Marlins must get him on the mound if only to force a trade, as the
club can't afford his $7 million salary. Lowell and Kevin Orie will
fight it out for third base, and rookie SS Alex Rodriguez inherits
Renteria's old spot.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $12 box seats, $9 reserved, $5 general
admission. Telephone: 407-633-9200.
</P>
<P>
   MONTREAL EXPOS
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: Roger Dean Stadium (7,200); Jupiter, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 65-97 (4th).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Felipe Alou (eighth season, 535-496).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: LHP Roberto Duran and OF Manny Martinez.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: OF F.P. Santangelo.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: Alou must find a left fielder, selecting from
James Mouton and Orlando Merced. The last two spots of the rotation
must be filled out behind Dustin Hermanson, Carl Pavano and Javier
Vazquez. Mike Thurman and L.A. export Ted Lilly are in line.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $15 box seats, $13 loge, $9 grand stand,
$5 general admission. Telephone: 888-447-4824.
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK METS
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: St. Lucie County Stadium (7,347); Port St.
Lucie, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 88-74 (2nd).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Bobby Valentine (fourth season, 188-167; overall,
769-772).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: RHP Armando Benitez, OF Bobby Bonilla, OF Roger
Cedeno, INF Mariano Duncan, OF Rickey Henderson and 3B Robin
Ventura.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: 2B Carlos Baerga, RHP Willie Blair, OF Lenny Harris,
C Todd Hundley, OF Butch Huskey, OF Tony Phillips, RHP Armando
Reynoso and RHP Mel Rojas.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: Bonilla, counted on to be the every-day right
fielder, is recovering from several maladies, most of all a bad
wrist. Foremost, Mets brass want to see results.
</P>
<P>
   Spring ticket info: $12 box seats, $9 reserved. Telephone:
561-871-2115.
</P>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA PHILLIES
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: Jack Russell Memorial Stadium (6,882);
Clearwater, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 75-87 (3rd).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Terry Francona (third season, 143-181).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: RHP Jeff Brantley, OF Rob Ducey, LF Ron Gant, OF
David Miller, RHP Chad Ogea, C Tom Prince, RHP Cliff Politte and
LHP Paul Spoljaric.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: OF Ruben Amaro, RHP Ricky Bottalico, RHP Mark
Leiter, 2B Mark Lewis, C Mark Parent, RHP Mark Portugal and RHP
Jerry Spradlin.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: The rotation remains unsettled after Curt
Schilling, Carlton Loewer and Chad Ogea. Ex-Braves player Paul Byrd
is in the mix, but the club still wants L.A.'s Dave Mlicki.
Brantley's shoulder remains suspect, and the closer job is open.
Rookie 2B Marlon Anderson must be ready for prime time. The
position is his; no options.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $12 box seats, $6 through $11 for
reserved. Telephone: 727-442-8496.
</P>
<P>
   NL CENTRAL
</P>
<P>
   CHICAGO CUBS
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: HoHoKam Park (12,500), Mesa, Ariz.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Friday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 90-73 (2nd).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Jim Riggleman (fifth season, 307-324; overall,
419-503).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: RHP Jon Lieber, RHP Scott Sanders and C Benito
Santiago.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: OF Brant Brown, RHP Mark Clark and C Scott Servais.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: The clock is ticking for the Cubs, who do not
start a player younger than 30. First, they need reassurance on
phenom Kerry Wood's elbow. Wood went through a rigorous offseason
training program after a strain sidelined him for September. Sammy
Sosa's winter was more exhausting than the last weeks of 1998.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $13 field box, $12 terrace box, $10
terrace/field, $6 general admission. Telephone: 602-964-4467.
</P>
<P>
   CINCINNATI REDS
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: Ed Smith Stadium (7,500), Sarasota, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 77-85 (4th).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Jack McKeon (third season, 110-115; overall,
589-589).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: LHP Steve Avery, OF Mike Cameron, C Brian Johnson,
INF Mark Lewis, 1B Hal Morris, LHP Denny Neagle and OF Michael
Tucker.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: 2B Bret Boone, OF Melvin Nieves, 1B Eduardo Perez
and LHP Mike Remlinger.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: McKeon will be busy. He has competition going
at four positions _ center field (Cameron and Jeffrey Hammonds),
right field (Tucker and Dmitri Young), first base (Morris and Sean
Casey) and catcher (Johnson and Eddie Taubensee). Stan Belinda
(4-8, 3.23) is coming back after a late-season diagnosis of
multiple sclerosis.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $10 box, $8 reserved, $5 general
admission. Telephone: 941-954-4464.
</P>
<P>
