</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: Osceola County Stadium (5,130), Kissimmee, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 102-60 (1st).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Larry Dierker (third season, 186138).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: 3B Ken Caminiti, RHP Xavier Hernandez and RHP Brian
Powell.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: C Brad Ausmus, 3B Sean Berry, LHP Randy Johnson, LHP
Mike Magnante and LHP C.J. Nitkowski.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: Their hopes for acquiring Roger Clemens
dashed, the Astros try to build a rotation around Shane Reynolds
and Mike Hampton that might offset the loss of Johnson. Fat chance.
Caminiti reintroduces himself at third base, and rookie Mitch
Meluskey has an opportunity to earn time at catcher.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $12 box, $10 reserved, $7 general
admission. Telephone 407-933-2520.
