<P>
   NL WEST
</P>
<P>
   ARIZONA DIAMONDBACKS
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: Tucson Electric Park (11,000), Tucson, Ariz.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 65-97 (5th).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Buck Showalter (second season, 65-97, overall,
377-366).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: 1B Greg Colbrunn, OF Steve Finley, LHP Randy
Johnson, OF Luis Gonzalez, OF Dante Powell, RHP Armando Reynoso,
RHP Todd Stottlemyre and LHP Greg Swindell.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: LHP Joel Adamson, RHP Willie Banks, OF Brant Brede,
LHP Alan Embree, OF Karim Garcia, RHP Felix Rodriguez, OF Devon
White and RHP Bob Wolcott.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: The D-Backs would like a reassurance that
closer Gregg Olson's (30 saves, 3.01 ERA) arm troubles are behind
him. The club also needs 3B Matt Williams to bounce back after a
20-homer, 71-RBI year. Dealing OF Bernard Gilkey's $11 million
contract is a priority.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $14 club, $12 field level/infield, $9
field level outfield. $6 bleachers, $3 lawn. Telephone:
888-777-4664.
</P>
<P>
   COLORADO ROCKIES
</P>
<P>
   _ Training site: Hi Corbett Field (10,000), Tucson, Ariz.
</P>
<P>
   _ First full squad workout: Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   _ 1998 record: 77-85 (4th).
</P>
<P>
   _ Manager: Jim Leyland (first season; overall, 997-1,041).
</P>
<P>
   _ Newcomers: LHP Brian Bohanon and OF Lenny Harris.
</P>
<P>
   _ Departed: RHP Roger Bailey, INF Jason Bates, LHP Mike Munoz
and RHP Mark Thompson.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring projects: No Rockies starter had a winning record last
year, a cue to Darryl Kile and Pedro Astacio if this team is going
anywhere. Leyland still has no closer and will use a committee,
unless Jerry DiPoto, Mike DeJean or Curtis Leskanic seizes the job.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spring ticket info: $12 box, $11 home plate grandstand, $10
lower grandstand, $9 upper grandstand, $8 pavilion, $4 bleachers.
Telephone: 800-388-ROCK.
</P>
