<P>
   BKC-GATECH-MARYLAND _ The loss of center Obinna Ekezie was a
major blow for the Maryland Terrapins, who were expected to contend
for the national championship this season. In an odd development,
however, Ekezie's absence has energized the team. The Terps are
playing stronger defense, everyone apparently improving to
compensate for the loss of Ekezie. Now coach Gary Williams has a
much quicker team on the floor, which is why they pounded North
Carolina last Saturday. They had the whole week off before playing
Georgia Tech and finish against Clemson and Florida State.Now, the
Terps are once again excited and focused on winning the ACC.
(Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20. MOVED.
