<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sunday, Feb. 21, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   (EDITORS: Adding late DEATH-OF-SALESMAN, a copyrighted story.)
</P>
<P>
   DEATH-OF-SALESMAN (Los Angeles) _ Chris Rawlings, who died
earlier this month after a `home-invasion robbery,' was a
boyish-looking 30-year-old with a lot of flash, but oh how he could
sell the adult's dream of fast, hard, cold cash. The Los Angeles
Daily News profiles the life-and-death of a con artist. By Beth
Barrett. (Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news
files.)
</P>
<P>
   STRAY-DOGS (Los Angeles) _ It took a trio of Los Angeles animal
control officers less than three hours to snag 20 stray dogs in one
10-block area in an east San Fernando Valley neighborhood, barely
putting a dent in the city's feral dog problem. By Phil Davis.
(Will move on the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   LAW-BOOK (Ventura, Calif.) _ Researching closing arguments
during law school, Michael Lief discovered there were no
anthologies of the more successful summations in legal history, so
he decided to create one. Now, Lief is a deputy district attorney,
and best-selling author. By Don Holland. (Will move on the ``n''
California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
</TEXT>
