 CLEMENS SKIPS TEXAS FOR BETTER SERIES
SHOT (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) By T.R. SULLIVAN
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; P &QR;  &LR; bu:Star-Telegram Staff Writer
 &LR; body: &QL; z10 &QR;  &QL; B &QR; TAMPA, Fla. Q  &QL; z10.8 &QR;  &QL; P &QR; Roger ClemensU agent said the
chance to
win a World Series was the main reason he accepted a trade to the
New York Yankees rather than hold out for a chance to pitch with
the Rangers.  &QL; P &QR; Randy Hendricks said yesterday the Yankees were
three times more likely to
win the World Series than the Rangers and that was more important
than ClemensU desire to pitch in Texas.  &QL; P &QR; Hendricks, arriving with
Clemens yesterday at the Yankees spring training
facility, was reacting to Rangers general manager Doug MelvinUs
comments last week when the Toronto Blue Jays traded the five-time
Cy Young Award winner to New York.  &QL; P &QR; Clemens, who lives outside
Houston, had the right to veto any trade
according to an agreement between Clemens and the Blue Jays. Melvin
said he was misled into believing ClemensU No. 1 goal was to pitch
close to home when he originally demanded a trade from the Blue
Jays last November.  &QL; P &QR; RI think there was some frustration on
DougUs part because he had been
working hard on this for two months,S said Hendricks, who accused
the Rangers of whining. RWe have a good relationship with Doug and
a high regard for him, but heUs taking into consideration just one
part of the equation. HeUs not considering the [World Series] ring
factor.  &QL; P &QR; RRoger wants to win a World Series. ThereUs a
distinction between being
qualified to make the playoffs and being qualified to win the World
Series. The Yankees are the most qualified to win the World Series.
The Yankees have a 60 percent chance of winning the World Series,
the Rangers have a 20 percent chance.S  &QL; P &QR; Melvin, reached at the
RangersU camp in Port Charlotte, said, RThatUs fine,
but say that from the start. Say your No. 1 priority is to go to
New York and if it doesnUt work out, get back to us. We thought he
wanted to be closer to home.S  &QL; P &QR; The Rangers thought they had
Clemens on Wednesday for outfielder Ruben
Mateo and two other players. But Toronto general manager Gord Ash
made one more call to the Yankees and instead traded Clemens to the
defending world champions for pitchers David Wells and Graeme Lloyd
and second baseman Homer Bush.  &QL; P &QR; Clemens, talking before his first
workout with the Yankees, said he had no
idea the Rangers had worked out a deal with the Blue Jays.  &QL; P &QR; RA
week ago I was planning to be [with the Blue Jays],S Clemens said.
RI
didnUt think anything was happening. It was real quiet until Randy
called late in the evening Wednesday.  &QL; P &QR; RHe said a trade was
imminent, said it was the Yankees and asked, is it on
or isnUt it. I said letUs go.S  &QL; P &QR; Asked about his stated desire to
pitch in Texas, Clemens said, RWeUve
talked about that many times. It would have been great. ItUs
hindsight now.  &QL; P &QR; RIUm excited to be here. This is a great
opportunity for me. I have an
opportunity to go out there in Yankee Stadium and be a part of
tradition, the monuments ... itUs exciting. I canUt wait to get out
there.S  &QL; P &QR; Hendricks also said the Rangers should have been willing
to give up Mateo
before Wednesday.  &QL; P &QR; RRuben Mateo was asked for by the Blue Jays
from December through
February,S Hendricks said. RIt was not until this week he was
included. If Roger was that important to them, why was Ruben Mateo
not included before so we could have been presented with a trade in
January?  &QL; P &QR; RThatUs my answer to the Texas RangersU public whining
about Roger.S
 &QL; P &QR; But Melvin said, RRuben Mateo earlier wouldnUt have gotten the
deal done.
We were still talking about Ruben Mateo, plus other players. For
example, Mateo and [Rick] Helling, which we didnUt want to do.S
 &QL; P &QR; Melvin said he has not spoken to Hendricks or his brother Alan
since the
trade was completed but will try to call them tomorrow.
</P>
