<SLUG> BC-BKC-ASU-OREGONST.-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GRITTY ASU EFFORT GIVES EVANS 100TH WIN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - When Rob Evans spoke of his team being committed
Saturday, he wasn't referring to a place with straitjackets and
barred windows.
</P>
<P>
   Although the team's sloppy loss to Oregon on Thursday probably
had the Arizona State coach pondering such options, its effort
Saturday in an 87-66 victory over Oregon State gave him hope.
</P>
<P>
   ``I could tell early on we were committed to winning this
basketball game,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Evans picked up his 100th victory and the Sun Devils kept their
very, very slim hopes for a spot in the NCAA Tournament alive with
a convincing win in front of 5,002 at Wells Fargo Arena.
</P>
<P>
   ASU (14-12 overall) takes over fifth place in the Pac-10 with a
6-8 record. The Sun Devils would need to win their remaining four
to have a shot.
</P>
<P>
   ASU dominated Saturday with its best defensive effort of the
season and one of its best overall performances. It forced a
season-high 24 turnovers with the help of 12 steals. The offense
fed off the intensity and got 23 points from Bobby Lazor, who
became the first two-year player in school history to score 1,000.
</P>
<P>
   ``Right now, we're just thinking, `Win one, win one, win one,
win one,' '' center Mike Batiste said. ``That's the only way we can
do it.''
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Devils shot 52.5 percent from the field, their best
effort in 11 games and only the fourth time this season they've
surpassed 50 percent. They are 4-0 when they do.
</P>
<P>
   Evans was concerned coming into the game. The Sun Devils were
coming off a 76-75 loss to the Ducks in which they started off the
game 3 for 21 from the field. They were much sharper Saturday,
trailing just once early and leading by 10 less than seven minutes
into the game.
</P>
<P>
   `You know your own kids,'' Evans said. ``You just have a feel
for it. And I could see the seriousness as we were leaving the
locker room. There was no kidding around.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is one of the most complete games they've played on the
defensive end of the floor and executing on the offensive end.''
</P>
<P>
   The win avenged an 81-51 loss to the Beavers in Corvallis on
Jan. 21. The day after that game, Oregon State guard Deaundra
Tanner told a local paper he tried to defend House like he was ``a
girlfriend,'' suggesting he tried to stick as close to the guard as
he could.
</P>
<P>
   But House and his teammates took the comment as derogatory, and
used it as fuel in Saturday's game.
</P>
<P>
   ``Whenever you go into somebody's house and they disrespect you,
you keep it in the back of your mind,'' Batiste said. ``You want to
get back at them.''
</P>
<P>
   They did and then some. The Beavers (12-12, 6-9) fall to 0-8 on
the road (vs. 6-1 at home) and are one game away from being the
first team in league history to lose all its road games and still
have a winning record at home.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it was a product of the (Sun Devils') energy and
aggressiveness,'' Oregon State Coach Eddie Payne said. ``They were
embarrassed in two ways: last Thursday night and the last time we
played them. They were ready to play today. They got us back on our
heels, and we weren't ready to respond.''
</P>
<P>
   Evans insists he didn't talk to his team about revenge.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't have a bone in my body that tries to get back at
anybody,'' he said. ``I've had so many things done to me in life,
that if I tried to get revenge on everybody, I'd waste a whole lot
of valuable time. Plus, we've lost 12 ballgames. So we'd have to
have a lot of revenge on people.''
</P>
<P>
   House finished with 16 points, seven assists and three rebounds.
Batiste had 15 points and eight rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Center Jason Heide led Oregon State with 18.
</P>
<P>
   ``We think we still have a chance (for the NCAA Tournament),''
House said. ``We're in fifth place alone and they could take five
teams. I don't even want to talk about the NIT.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've got to play every game like it's our last.'' &QL; 
Notes &QL; 
House's seven assists equaled his season high.
</P>
<P>
   The Beavers' 24 turnovers were a season high.
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Devils made 11 of 21 (52.4 percent) three-point shots.
</P>
<P>
   Both teams struggled from the free-throw line. ASU made 12 of 23
(52.2 percent). Oregon State hit 11 of 19 (57.9 percent). &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
