 (Eds.: Newspapers that used the Boston Globe story UMASS-ADMISSIONS
(a) by Cindy Rodriquez, which moved Feb. 19, will wish to use the
following corrective.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
A Boston Globe article about admissions policies at the University
of Massachusetts at Amherst incorrectly described court rulings
involving admission policies at Boston Latin School. In May 1998,
Chief U.S. District Judge Joseph L. Tauro upheld the Boston School
Department's race-based policy. His ruling was overturned by the
U.S. First Circuit Court of Appeals in November.
</P>
